<div class="c230_6">
<div id="v230.6.1"><span class="H5329 s">To the chief Musician</span><span class="H5058 s"> on Neginoth</span><span class="H8067 s"> upon Sheminith</span><span class="H4210 s">, A Psalm</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H3068 s">. O LORD</span><span class="H3198 s">, rebuke</span><span class="H639 s"> me not in thine anger</span><span class="H3256 s">, neither chasten</span><span class="H2534 s"> me in thy hot displeasure</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Sheminith: or, upon the eight)</span></div>
<div id="v230.6.2"><span class="H2603 s">Have mercy</span><span class="H3068 s"> upon me, O LORD</span><span class="H536 s">; for I <i>am</i> weak</span><span class="H3068 s">: O LORD</span><span class="H7495 s">, heal</span><span class="H6106 s"> me; for my bones</span><span class="H926 s"> are vexed</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.6.3"><span class="H5315 s">My soul</span><span class="H3966 s"> is also sore</span><span class="H926 s"> vexed</span><span class="H3068 s">: but thou, O LORD</span>, how long?</div>
<div id="v230.6.4"><span class="H7725 s">Return</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H2502 s">, deliver</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span><span class="H3467 s">: oh save</span> me for thy mercies' H2617 sake.</div>
<div id="v230.6.5"><span class="H4194 s">For in death</span><span class="H2143 s"> <i>there is</i> no remembrance</span><span class="H7585 s"> of thee: in the grave</span><span class="H3034 s"> who shall give thee thanks</span>?</div>
<div id="v230.6.6"><span class="H3021 s">I am weary</span><span class="H585 s"> with my groaning</span><span class="H3915 s">; all the night</span><span class="H4296 s"> make I my bed</span><span class="H7811 s"> to swim</span><span class="H4529 s">; I water</span><span class="H6210 s"> my couch</span><span class="H1832 s"> with my tears</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (allâ€¦: or, every night)</span></div>
<div id="v230.6.7"><span class="H5869 s">Mine eye</span><span class="H6244 s"> is consumed</span><span class="H3708 s"> because of grief</span><span class="H6275 s">; it waxeth old</span><span class="H6887 s"> because of all mine enemies</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.6.8"><span class="H5493 s">Depart</span><span class="H6466 s"> from me, all ye workers</span><span class="H205 s"> of iniquity</span><span class="H3068 s">; for the LORD</span><span class="H8085 s"> hath heard</span><span class="H6963 s"> the voice</span><span class="H1065 s"> of my weeping</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.6.9"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H8085 s"> hath heard</span><span class="H8467 s"> my supplication</span><span class="H3068 s">; the LORD</span><span class="H3947 s"> will receive</span><span class="H8605 s"> my prayer</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.6.10"><span class="H341 s">Let all mine enemies</span><span class="H954 s"> be ashamed</span><span class="H3966 s"> and sore</span><span class="H926 s"> vexed</span><span class="H7725 s">: let them return</span><span class="H954 s"> <i>and</i> be ashamed</span><span class="H7281 s"> suddenly</span>.</div></div>
